# Archetype Sync Rule

When modifying **any** consumer or provider project, check whether the change affects a class that also exists as a template in the corresponding archetype.

> All projects are independent repos at `/Users/marcelosales/Development/swim/`. This rule applies regardless of which workspace is open.

## Scope

| Project modified | Archetype to check |
|---|---|
| `swim-digital-notam-consumer`, `swim-ed254-consumer`, `swim-ffice-consumer` | `../swim-consumer-archetype/` |
| `swim-digital-notam-provider`, `swim-ed254-provider`, `swim-ffice-provider` | `../swim-provider-archetype/` |

## Where the archetype templates live

```
/Users/marcelosales/Development/swim/swim-consumer-archetype/src/main/resources/archetype-resources/
  src/main/java/          # Consumer Java templates (Velocity)
  src/main/resources/     # Consumer application.properties template

/Users/marcelosales/Development/swim/swim-provider-archetype/src/main/resources/archetype-resources/
  src/main/java/          # Provider Java templates (Velocity)
  src/main/resources/     # Provider application.properties template
```

## What to check

1. **Structural changes**: New/deleted/renamed classes, moved packages
2. **Interface changes**: New methods in port interfaces, changed signatures
3. **Pattern changes**: New SPIs, new annotations, constructor changes
4. **Configuration changes**: New properties in `application.properties`, new Kafka/AMQP channels

## What to do

- **Mechanical/infrastructure classes** (REST, persistence, messaging, adapters, subscription): update archetype template
- **Domain-specific classes** (EventExtractor, EventData, FilterDimension): no archetype update needed (those are stubs)
- After updating:
  - Consumer: `cd /Users/marcelosales/Development/swim/swim-consumer-archetype && mvn clean install`
  - Provider: `cd /Users/marcelosales/Development/swim/swim-provider-archetype && mvn clean install`
- Use `${serviceName}`, `${package}`, etc. for parameterized values

## STOP and ASK the user

If unsure whether a project change should propagate to the archetype, STOP and ask before proceeding.
